note Open MPI 1.10.3 has just been released, and you should use it,<div>install procedure of 1.8.1 should work too.</div><div><br></div><div>what is exactly the issue ?</div><div>the fortran wrapper is mpifort, mpif90 is just an alias.</div><div>is there a Fortran compiler on your system ?</div><div>if not, just install one and re configure/make install</div><div><br></div>strictly speaking, there is no fortran 77 vs 90 vs 2008, but<div>include &#39;mpif.h&#39;</div><div>vs</div><div>use mpi</div><div>vs</div><div>use mpi_f08</div><div><br></div><div>if you need </div><div>use mpi</div><div>support, usually but incorrectly referred as f90 support, you can</div><div>configure --enable-mpi-fortran=usempi</div><div><div>it will abort if your compiler cannot build that,</div><div>please post the configure output and config.log so we can have a look</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Cheers,</div><div><br></div><div>Gilles</div><div><br>On Wednesday, June 22, 2016, mayank bhuwal &lt;<a href="mailto:mayankwondorous2789@gmail.com">mayankwondorous2789@gmail.com</a>&gt; wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex"><div dir="ltr"><div style="font-size:12.8px">I have installed OpenMPI following the instruction given in the below link :</div><div style="font-size:12.8px"><a href="http://sysads.co.uk/2014/05/install-open-mpi-1-8-ubuntu-14-04-13-10/" target="_blank">http://sysads.co.uk/2014/05/install-open-mpi-1-8-ubuntu-14-04-13-10/</a><br></div><div style="font-size:12.8px"><br></div><div style="font-size:12.8px">Also i have checked that mpif90 is present inside the bin folder of openmpi.</div><div style="font-size:12.8px"><br></div><div style="font-size:12.8px"><br></div><div><br></div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Wed, Jun 22, 2016 at 5:01 PM, mayank bhuwal <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="javascript:_e(%7B%7D,&#39;cvml&#39;,&#39;mayankwondorous2789@gmail.com&#39;);" target="_